This paper deals with the analysis of large mobile phone calling networks, which is a topic that falls under the purview of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper focuses on the statistical properties of social networks constructed from mobile phone calling records. The second likely category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper may involve the development of algorithms and software tools for analyzing large-scale communication networks. The third likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), as the paper uses computational methods to study social phenomena. The fourth likely category is cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy), as the paper may involve the analysis of privacy and security issues related to mobile phone communication. The fifth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with the analysis of communication networks.
